{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsUhEAg3RkCMSmj3d4dq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is healthy. Summary:\n\n**Root cause found:** the `ingress-nginx-controller` pod was stuck `Pending` — its pod spec requires the node label `ingress-ready=true`, which wasn't set on the single node.\n\n**Changes made:**\n1. Labeled the node: `kubectl label node karma-7-control-plane ingress-ready=true` → controller scheduled and became `Running`/`Ready`.\n2. Generated a self-signed TLS cert for `es.example.com` and stored it as `Secret/es-tls` in the `elasticsearch` namespace.\n3. Created `Ingress/es-http` in `elasticsearch` using `ingressClassName: nginx`, routing `es.example.com` → `es-http:9200`, with TLS configured and `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/ssl-redirect: \"true\"` / `force-ssl-redirect: \"true\"` so plain HTTP is redirected (308) instead of served.\n\n**Verified:**\n- `https://es.example.com/` → `200` with the Elasticsearch API JSON response.\n- `http://es.example.com/` → `308` redirect to HTTPS (no API data over plain HTTP).\n- Elasticsearch cluster remains `green`, 3/3 nodes, all pods healthy."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":688,"cache_read_input_tokens":86187,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":688},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d9924ba7-a8b5-4bf8-9057-dc61b8f6ac2e","uuid":"22be8c78-e20e-4382-b963-2f09f271ec01","request_id":"req_011CcsUhCvmA2g5Q2fFebdPY"}
